This paper deals with the problem of adaptive streaming over the Internet, which involves network measurements and prediction algorithms. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of heuristics and optimization techniques to maximize the quality of experience, which suggests that it could also be classified under Information Theory (cs.IT) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm under different experimental conditions, which could make it relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
